.TH "HTMLDIALOGELEMENT.CLOSE_EVENT" "3JS" "January 26, 2026" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
HTMLDialogElement.close_event \- HTMLDialogElement: close event
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[CR]close\f[R] event is fired on an \f[CR]HTMLDialogElement\f[R]
object when the \f[CR]<dialog>\f[R] it represents has been closed.
.PP
This event is not cancelable and does not bubble.
.SH SYNTAX
Use the event name in methods like \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], or set
an event handler property.
.IP
.EX
addEventListener(\(dqclose\(dq, (event) => { })

onclose = (event) => { }
.EE
.SH EVENT TYPE
A generic \f[CR]Event\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Handling \f[CR]close\f[R] events
This example demonstrates how to listen for \f[CR]close\f[R] events
triggered by several different methods for closing a dialog:
.IP \(bu 2
Calling the \f[CR]close()\f[R] method
.IP \(bu 2
A form with \f[CR]method=\(dqdialog\(dq\f[R].
Submitting the form closes the \f[CR]dialog\f[R] and causes a
\f[CR]submit\f[R] event to be fired, without submitting data or clearing
the form
.IP \(bu 2
The Esc key.
See \f[CR]cancel\f[R] event
.SS HTML
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]dialog\f[R] id=\(dqdialog\(dq>
  <\f[B]form\f[R] method=\(dqdialog\(dq>
    <\f[B]button\f[R] type=\(dqsubmit\(dq>Close via method=\(dqdialog\(dq</\f[B]button\f[R]>
  </\f[B]form\f[R]>
  <\f[B]p\f[R]><\f[B]button\f[R] id=\(dqclose\(dq>Close via .close() method</\f[B]button\f[R]></\f[B]p\f[R]>
  <\f[B]p\f[R]>Or hit the <\f[B]kbd\f[R]>Esc</\f[B]kbd\f[R]> key</\f[B]p\f[R]>
</\f[B]dialog\f[R]>

<\f[B]button\f[R] id=\(dqopen\(dq>Open dialog</\f[B]button\f[R]>
.EE
.SS JavaScript
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] dialog = document.getElementById(\(dqdialog\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] openButton = document.getElementById(\(dqopen\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] closeButton = document.getElementById(\(dqclose\(dq);

openButton.addEventListener(\(dqclick\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  log(\(dqopen button click event fired\(dq, \f[B]true\f[R]);
  log(\(dqdialog showModal() called\(dq);
  dialog.showModal();
});

closeButton.addEventListener(\(dqclick\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  log(\(dqclose button click event fired\(dq);
  log(\(dqdialog close() called\(dq);
  dialog.close();
});

dialog.addEventListener(\(dqclose\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  log(\(dqdialog close event fired\(dq);
});
.EE
.SS Result
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
HTML \f[CR]<dialog>\f[R] element
